[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I wonder how we look to the people around us?[r]
Sisters with an age gap? I hope we don't look like a parent and child, but we probably don't look like friends either.[l][r]
To be honest, even when I think about our relationship, it's very odd. Are we friends? Comrades? Nothing seems to fit.[l][r]
... War buddies? No, that's close but not quite right...[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Ishii, do you perhaps have a stomachache?"[l][r]
"No...? Not at all. Why do you ask?"[l][r]
"It's just that you seem uneasy."[l][r]
"Do I?"[r]
"Yeah."[l][r]
Chito nodded as if it was something obvious. I guess I look stressed, then. I took a deep breath to recenter myself and dropped my relaxing shoulders.[l][r]
"Would you like a drink?"[l][r]
Chito offered me her canteen. I squinted at it; it looked far too rugged and utilitarian for a girl her age.[l][r]
"Thanks... what's in it, tea?"[r]
"Tap water. Dechlorinated."[l][r]
"... Sure, I'll have some."[r]
"Here you go."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I took a drink from Chito's canteen and thanked her, handing it back. She took a sip herself, closing the cap with a small smile on her lips.[l][r]
"You look like you're having fun."[r]
"Yeah, I'm having fun. Also, I'm looking forward to seeing it."[l][r]
"The Kettenkrad?"[r]
"Yes... but I might cry when it happens."[l][r]
"... It's okay to cry, you know."[r]
"Yeah."[l][r]

This conversation is, admittedly, pretty weird, but I'm having a lot of fun. It's strange; feeling happy seems like a rare occasion nowadays.[r]
It reminds me of the time when the three of us were recklessly building that airplane at the base, even if Yuuri isn't here with us this time around.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

