"Hey, Chito," I spoke quietly, practically whispering into her ear.[r]
"... Is that 'fog' going to bother you today?"[l][r]
"No. It appeared again this morning, but I took care of it."[l][r]
"Why didn't you tell me sooner?," was what I wanted to say, but—[r]
"It's fine," Chito shrugged, her tone so casual... as if it was nothing.[l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

