I wanted to say that. I really, really wanted to say that.[l][r]
... But I couldn’t.[l][r]
Because she's smart. Because she already knows.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I silently gave Chito's hand a light squeeze.[l][r]
"... Ishii?"[r]
"... If that's how you want it to be, fine.[l]... But if you ever need to let something off your chest, or a shoulder to cry on... please just tell me."[l][r]
"Yeah, I will.[r]
... Thank you."[r]
Chito mumbled before returning the squeeze.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Could I ask you something, then?"[r]
"Hm? What is it?"[l][r]
"My eyesight has been declining lately. What do you think I should get, glasses or contacts?"[r]
"Huh?"[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I must have looked stupid, freezing in place at Chito's sudden question. She, however, kept staring at me with a deadpan expression on her face.[l][r]
Taking advantage of my confusion, she swiftly reached out and yanked my glasses off my face.[l][r]
"H-Hey! What are you doing?"[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

