I get it now. She knows that herself, doesn't she?[l][r]
What has become of me? Ever since our paths crossed again, I can barely control my heart anymore.[l][r]

Chito handed me a handkerchief. I took off my glasses and thanked her for her thoughtfulness as I wiped the tears from the corners of my eyes. I handed it back, and she squeezed my hand in a reassuring gesture.[l][r]
That dainty, seemingly fragile hand calmed my pounding heart. I took a look at Chito, peering down towards her; her eyes met mine, staring right back up at me. A quiet, heartfelt "thank you" left her lips.[l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="station3.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Thanks to you and your care, I find the strength to keep going... even without Yuu."[l][r]
"But—... I—..."[l][r]
"It's alright. You matter to me too, Ishii. A lot."[r]
"..."[l][r]

The crowd bustling before me seemed so far away now. Everything around us seemed to grind to a halt, the noise of everyday chatter drowning out in the silence of this moment.[r]
I came to a realization. Recently, I found that... thing again. The blueprint for the airplane I built in the other world.[l][r]
Unable to bear dying a lonely, miserable death, I clung to it. I put all of my hopes, dreams and aspirations into it and what it meant to me...[l][r]
... and in the end, I, who should've died alone in this world, clung to this girl who found and relied on me the same way.[l][r]

There's no difference between the numerous strangers that crowded this station and the girl before me; aside from the fact that we once shared a home, hardship... and joy. Nothing else mattered.[l][r]

From a distance, I heard someone calling out to Chito and me.[l][r]
"It's Kanazawa. He's here, Ishii."[r]
"... Yeah."[l][r]
I closed my eyes and counted to three, calming my nerves the same way I did before taking off that fateful day.[l][r]
My eyes snapped open when my expression took on its usual strictness. I glanced towards the speeding couple and quickly got to reprimanding the two.[r]
"You're late. We've been waiting for a while, you know."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

